Gold miner Harmony Gold Mining reports that an employee had been fatally injured at its Moab Khotsong mine, in Orkney, in the North West, following an engineering-related incident on March 15. “Safety is a foundational value at Harmony and it is of utmost importance that we ensure a safe working environment at all our operations,” says Harmony CEO Peter Steenkamp. Harmony’s management team extends its condolences to the deceased’s family, friends and co-workers.